import numpy
n = int(input())
ar1 = []
ar2 = []
for i in range(n):
    tmp = list(map(int,input().split()))
    ar1.append(tmp)
np_ar1 = numpy.array(ar1)

    tmp = list(map(int,input().split()))

import numpy as np

n = int(input().strip())
arr1 = np.array([[int(x) for x in input().strip().split()] for _ in range(n)])
arr2 = np.array([[int(x) for x in input().strip().split()] for _ in range(n)])

print(np.dot(arr1, arr2))
